---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Plugins — KCode Docs">
  <section class="container doc-page">
    <nav class="breadcrumb">
      <a href="/docs">Docs</a> &rsaquo; <span>Plugins</span>
    </nav>

    <h1>Plugin System</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Extend KCode with custom skills, hooks, MCP servers, output styles, and agents.</p>

    <h2>Installing Plugins</h2>
    <p>Use the built-in marketplace to discover and install plugins:</p>
    <pre><code># Search for plugins
kcode plugin search "docker"

# Install a plugin
kcode plugin install kcode-docker

# List installed plugins
kcode plugin list

# Update all plugins
kcode plugin update

# Remove a plugin
kcode plugin remove kcode-docker</code></pre>

    <h2>Plugin Locations</h2>
    <p>Plugins can be installed globally or per-project:</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Location</th><th>Scope</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>~/.kcode/plugins/</code></td><td>Global</td><td>Available in all projects</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>.kcode/plugins/</code></td><td>Project</td><td>Only available in the current project (commit to share with team)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Plugin Structure</h2>
    <p>A plugin is a directory with a <code>plugin.json</code> manifest and optional component files:</p>
    <pre><code>my-plugin/
  plugin.json           # Required: manifest file
  skills/
    deploy.md           # Skill definitions (markdown or TypeScript)
    lint-check.md
  hooks/                # Hook scripts
    pre-commit.sh
  mcp-servers/
    my-server/          # Bundled MCP server
      index.js
  output-styles/
    compact.md          # Custom output style
  agents/
    reviewer.md         # Custom agent definition</code></pre>

    <h2>plugin.json Manifest</h2>
    <p>The manifest declares what the plugin provides:</p>
    <pre><code set:html={`{
  "name": "kcode-docker",
  "version": "1.2.0",
  "description": "Docker and Docker Compose management skills",
  "author": "astrolexis",
  "license": "MIT",
  "kcode": ">=1.7.0",
  "skills": [
    "skills/docker-build.md",
    "skills/docker-compose.md",
    "skills/dockerfile-lint.md"
  ],
  "hooks": {
    "post:Write": [
      {
        "match": { "file_path": "**/Dockerfile*" },
        "action": "run",
        "command": "hadolint",
        "args": ["$FILE_PATH"]
      }
    ],
    "session:start": [
      {
        "action": "run",
        "command": "docker",
        "args": ["info", "--format", "{{.ServerVersion}}"]
      }
    ]
  },
  "mcpServers": {
    "docker-mcp": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["mcp-servers/docker/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "DOCKER_HOST": "unix:///var/run/docker.sock"
      }
    }
  },
  "outputStyles": [
    "output-styles/compact.md"
  ],
  "agents": [
    "agents/container-debugger.md"
  ]
}`} /></pre>

    <h2>Manifest Fields</h2>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>name</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Unique plugin identifier</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>version</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Semver version</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>description</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Short description</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>author</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Author name or organization</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>license</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>SPDX license identifier</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>kcode</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Minimum KCode version (semver range)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>skills</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>No</td><td>Paths to skill definition files</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>hooks</code></td><td>object</td><td>No</td><td>Hook event handlers (see below)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>mcpServers</code></td><td>object</td><td>No</td><td>MCP server configurations</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>outputStyles</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>No</td><td>Custom output style definitions</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>agents</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>No</td><td>Custom agent definitions</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Creating a Plugin</h2>
    <p>Use the Plugin SDK to scaffold a new plugin:</p>
    <pre><code># Interactive scaffold
kcode plugin create

# Or specify options directly
kcode plugin create my-plugin \
  --description "My custom plugin" \
  --components skills,hooks,mcp</code></pre>
    <p>Available components: <code>skills</code>, <code>hooks</code>, <code>mcp</code>, <code>output-styles</code>, <code>agents</code>.</p>

    <h3>Validating</h3>
    <pre><code># Validate manifest and structure
kcode plugin validate ./my-plugin

# Run plugin tests
kcode plugin test ./my-plugin</code></pre>

    <h3>Publishing</h3>
    <pre><code># Publish to the KCode marketplace
kcode plugin publish ./my-plugin</code></pre>
    <p>
      Published plugins are signed with a SHA-256 checksum and verified on install.
      The marketplace CDN configuration can be customized in settings.
    </p>

    <h2>Hook Events</h2>
    <p>Plugins can respond to 25 lifecycle events. Key hook events:</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Event</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>session:start</code></td><td>When a new session begins</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>session:end</code></td><td>When a session ends</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>pre:Bash</code></td><td>Before a Bash command executes</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>post:Bash</code></td><td>After a Bash command completes</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>pre:Write</code></td><td>Before a file is written</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>post:Write</code></td><td>After a file is written</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>pre:Edit</code></td><td>Before a file edit</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>post:Edit</code></td><td>After a file edit</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>compaction</code></td><td>When context compaction occurs</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>error</code></td><td>When an error occurs during tool execution</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Hook Match Filters</h3>
    <p>Hooks can use <code>match</code> to filter when they fire:</p>
    <pre><code set:html={`{
  "post:Write": [
    {
      "match": { "file_path": "**/*.py" },
      "action": "run",
      "command": "ruff",
      "args": ["check", "--fix", "$FILE_PATH"]
    }
  ]
}`} /></pre>

    <h2>MCP Servers in Plugins</h2>
    <p>
      Plugins can bundle <a href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io">Model Context Protocol</a> servers.
      These are spawned automatically when the plugin loads and their tools become available with the
      <code>mcp__</code> prefix.
    </p>
    <pre><code set:html={`"mcpServers": {
  "my-server": {
    "command": "node",
    "args": ["mcp-servers/my-server/index.js"],
    "env": {
      "MY_API_KEY": "\${MY_API_KEY}"
    }
  }
}`} /></pre>
    <p>Environment variable interpolation (<code>$&#123;VAR&#125;</code>) is supported in the <code>env</code> block.</p>

    <h2>Workspace Trust</h2>
    <p>
      Hooks from project-scoped plugins (<code>.kcode/plugins/</code>) require workspace trust.
      KCode will prompt for confirmation before executing hooks from untrusted workspaces.
      Global plugins (<code>~/.kcode/plugins/</code>) are always trusted.
    </p>

    <h2>Auto-Generated Documentation</h2>
    <p>Generate documentation for your plugin automatically:</p>
    <pre><code>kcode plugin docs ./my-plugin</code></pre>

    <nav class="doc-nav">
      <a href="/docs/local-models">&larr; Local Models</a>
      <a href="/docs/enterprise-sso">Enterprise SSO &rarr;</a>
    </nav>
  </section>

  <style>
    .doc-page { padding: 2rem 0 4rem; max-width: 900px; }
    .breadcrumb { color: #888; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .breadcrumb a { color: #7c8cf8; text-decoration: none; }
    .subtitle { color: #888; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: #e0e0e0; }
    h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #c9d1d9; font-size: 1.1rem; }
    pre { background: #0d1117; border: 1px solid #333; border-radius: 6px; padding: 1rem; overflow-x: auto; margin: 0.75rem 0; }
    code { color: #c9d1d9; font-size: 0.9rem; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
    th, td { text-align: left; padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #333; }
    th { color: #888; font-weight: 600; }
    td code { background: #1a1a2e; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; }
    ul { margin: 0.75rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
    li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    a { color: #7c8cf8; }
    .doc-nav { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid #333; }
    .doc-nav a { color: #7c8cf8; text-decoration: none; }
  </style>
</Base>
